comments: Hardaway Jr. (DAL) legally contests Leonard's (LAC) jump shot attempt.
Hardaway Jr. (DAL) makes marginal contact with Leonard (LAC) as the he releases from the pick.
Leonard (LAC) intentionally kicks the ball.
Leonard (LAC) and Hardaway Jr. (DAL) briefly engage and disengage following the pick
Leonard (LAC) makes contact to Hardaway Jr.'s (DAL) wrist after the release that affects his ability to follow through during the jump shot attempt.
At the end of the drive, Leonard (LAC) extends his arm into Kleber (DAL) to create space.
Finney-Smith (DAL) establishes himself in a legal picking position in Leonard's (LAC) path.
Leonard (LAC) maintains legal guarding position during Doncic's (DAL) drive.
Doncic (DAL) makes marginal contact with Leonard (LAC) with his off-arm as he steps back.
Doncic (DAL) gathers the ball and takes two legal steps prior to his shot attempt.
Kleber (DAL) engages and disengages with Morris Sr. (LAC) during the rebound.
Curry (DAL) is drawn into the air towards Williams (LAC) and he makes body contact that affects his jump shot attempt.
George (LAC) makes marginal contact with Kleber (DAL) as he secures the rebound.
George (LAC) briefly places an arm to Kleber (DAL) off ball but does not affect his FOM.
Morris Sr. (LAC) makes marginal contact with Doncic's (DAL) arm as he prepares to pass.
Leonard (LAC) momentarily places a hand to Curry's (DAL) front but immediately removes it and does not make any contact that affects Curry's SQBR.
Curry's (DAL) shot attempt fails to make contact with the rim and a shot clock violation is correctly awarded.
Hardaway Jr. (DAL) legally contest Leonard's (LAC) jump shot attempt.
Finney-Smith (DAL) establishes himself in a legal picking position in Leonard's (LAC) path.
Burke (DAL) places his off-arm against Morris Sr. (LAC) but the contact is marginal when he releases during the drive.
Morris Sr. (LAC) legally defends Burke's (DAL) driving shot attempt.
Doncic (DAL) avoids making contact with George (LAC) as he contests his driving shot attempt.
George (LAC) makes contact with the ball and then makes marginal contact with Kleber's (DAL) arm that does not affect his ability to secure the rebound.
George (LAC) legally contests Doncic's (DAL) jump shot attempt.
Burke (DAL) makes contact with Williams' (LAC) arm during his driving shot attempt.
Finney-Smith (DAL) makes incidental foot to foot contact with Williams (LAC) as he goes to, but not through Williams at the end of the drive.
Morris Sr. (LAC) makes marginal contact with Finney-Smith (DAL) after the release of the pass.
Morris Sr. (LAC) maintains a legal defensive position and does not make contact with Doncic's (DAL) arm during his driving shot attempt.
Morris Sr. (LAC) establishes himself in a legal screening position in Kleber's (DAL) path.
Kleber (DAL) legally contest Leonard's (LAC) jump shot attempt.
Hardaway Jr. (DAL) establishes himself in a legal picking position in Leonard's (DAL) path.
Jackson (LAC) maintains a legal defensive position as he defends Doncic's (DAL) driving shot attempt.
Doncic (DAL) gathers the ball and legally takes two steps to the basket during the spin move.
Hardaway Jr. (DAL) briefly grasps Williams' (LAC) arm as he moves off ball, but the contact is marginal.
Kleber (DAL) legally contest Morris Sr.'s (LAC) jump shot attempt.
Hardaway Jr. (DAL) establishes himself in a legal picking position in Leonard's (LAC) path.
Jackson (LAC) commits a take foul on Doncic (DAL).
Kleber (DAL) establishes himself in a legal screening position in Leonard's (LAC) path.  The two players briefly engage and disengage following the screen.
Jackson (LAC) legally contest Doncic's (DAL) jump shot attempt.
